data.description: So many possibilities with this home in the heart of Benton and in a price range rarely found in the area. Fresh paint throughout, new vinyl flooring and carpeting in all areas except bathrooms and kitchen; bedroom no. 3 currently does not have a closet and has a sunroom nearby that could possibly be converted to a closet. Front of the home is a neutral white and is waiting on your personal touches to bring personality to the exterior. Metal roof, generator, gas tankless water heater have been installed by current sellers. The quanset hut is being utilized as a shop with a car lift, shelving and 220 electrical. Property faces Poplar Street but is accessed through an alleyway off Denton Street which means very little traffic. Space for stackable washer and dryer in bathroom. Seller says hardwood floors under floor coverings in living area and two bedrooms. Agents: Call your investors or buyers who are looking for affordable housing who may want to add their personal touches. SF is approximate. County records shows 992 sf which was before bedroom/bathroom were added on carport end according to sellers.
